.TH inwstr 3
.SH NAME
\*Linwstr\*O, \*Linnwstr\*O, \*Lwinwstr\*O, \*Lwinnwstr\*O, \*Lmvinwstr\*O, \*Lmvinnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwinwstr\*O, \*Lmvwinnwstr\*O \- Get a string of wchar_t characters from a curses window
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
The \*Lcurses\*O library (\*Llibcurses.so\*O, \*Llibcurses.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O
.PP
\*Lint inwstr( wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint innwstr(
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint winwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint winnwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvinwstr(
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvinnwstr(
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvwinwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvwinnwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.sE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
.VL
.LI "\*Vwstr\*O"
Specifies the buffer for storing the wide-character string returned
from the window.
.LI "\*Vwin\*O"
Specifies a \*Lcurses\*O window. If not specified, the
window is the default window \*Lstdscr\*O.
.LI "\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O"
Specifies the line (\*Vy\*O) and column (\*Vx\*O)
coordinates of the target position on the window.
If coordinates are not specified, the target
position is the current position of the logical cursor.
.LI "\*Vn\*O"
Specifies the maximum number of wide characters to be returned
for the string.
.LE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "inwstr macro"
.iX "innwstr macro"
.iX "winwstr macro"
.iX "winnwstr subroutine"
.iX "mvinwstr macro"
.iX "mvinnwstr macro"
.iX "mvwinwstr macro"
.iX "mvwinnwstr macro"
The \*Linwstr\*O routine returns a string of wchar_t characters in \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at the current coordinates.
.PP
The \*Linnwstr\*O routine returns at most \*Vn\*O wchar_t characters in the
pointer \*Vwstr\*O on the default window at the current coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lwinwstr\*O routine returns a string of wchar_t characters in \*Vwstr\*O
on window \*Vwin\*O at the current coordinates.
.PP
The routine \*Lwinnwstr\*O returns at most \*Vn\*O wchar_t characters in the
pointer \*Vwstr\*O on window \*Vwin\*O at the current coordinates.
.PP
The routine \*Lmvinwstr\*O
returns a string of wchar_t characters in \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at coordinates (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O).
.PP
The routine \*Lmvinnwstr\*O returns at most \*Vn\*O wchar_t characters in the
pointer \*Vwstr\*O on the default window at
coordinates (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O).
.PP
The routine \*Lmvwinwstr\*O returns a string of
wchar_t characters in \*Vwstr\*O
on window \*Vwin\*O at coordinates (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O).
.PP
The routine \*Lmvwinnwstr\*O returns at most \*Vn\*O wchar_t characters in the
pointer \*Vwstr\*O on window \*Vwin\*O at the
coordinates (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O).
.PP
The following information applies to all the routines.
For all routines, the returned wchar_t character string ends at
the right margin of the line in the window.
For those four routines with \*Vn\*O as the last argument, at most \*Vn\*O
wchar_t characters are returned in the pointer \*Vwstr\*O.
.PP
The
\*Linwstr\*O, \*Linnwstr\*O, \*Lwinwstr\*O,
\*Lmvinwstr\*O, \*Lmvinnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwinwstr\*O, and \*Lmvwinnwstr\*O
routines are macros.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Linwstr\*O, \*Linnwstr\*O, \*Lwinwstr\*O, \*Lwinnwstr\*O,
\*Lmvinwstr\*O, \*Lmvinnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwinwstr\*O, and \*Lmvwinnwstr\*O
functions return \*LOK\*O on success and \*LERR\*O on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
